summary: Highlights include "Superheroes," with Colin as Magnet Man, Ryan as Mesmerized by Moving Objects Man, Chip as The Bob Fosse Kid and Wayne as The Chain Saw Massacre Boy; "Duet," in which Wayne and Chip sing a song about a sponge in the style of Busby Berkeley; "Weird Newscasters," with Chip as Snagglepuss, Wayne as a sportscaster who gives his peeping-tom neighbor a show, and Ryan doing weather as a Hollywood film legend from the silver screen era; "Newsflash"; an "Irish Drinking Song" about giving birth, and Drew joins in for "Themed Restaurant."

name: Keegan-Michael Key 5
summary: Hosted by comedian Aisha Tyler, cast members Ryan Stiles, Wayne Brady and Colin Mochrie, along with guest comedian Keegan-Michael Key, put their comedic skills to the test through a series of spontaneous improv games that are prompted only by random ideas supplied by the studio audience. The four performers must use the little information they have and their wild imaginations to depict different characters and an array of scenes, as well as perform songs. After each round of improvisation, Aisha will dole out points to our four performers and declare a winner at the end of every episode.
